cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TCS, cs.FL, cs.SE 

The paper deals with the extension of Turing machines to handle infinite alphabets, which is a topic related to logic and automata theory (cs.LO) as well as theoretical computer science (cs.TCS). The paper also discusses the pi-calculus, which is a process calculus used for modeling concurrent systems (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper introduces a new expressiveness criterion for process calculi, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and formal languages (cs.FL).
